               <head>Mirza Ja'far, letters</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Gul-i Jaʿfarī by Āftāb Rāy bin Munshīʾ Lamūdhar Pandit</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129379 http://lccn.loc.gov/n80132816 http://lccn.loc.gov/n2009200816 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115920 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85017991" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4065-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7052">Āftāb Rāy bin Munshīʾ Lamūdhar Pandit</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7052" type="supplied">آفتاب راى بن منشئ لمودهر پندت</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21975">Gul-i Jaʿfarī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21975">گل جعفرى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Excerpt from a larger collection of the official and private letters purported to be by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7677" role="aut">Fakhr al-Dīn Aḥmad Khān</persName>, known as <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7706" role="aut">Mīrzā Jaʿfar</persName>
                        </p>
                        <p>According to the preface, the letters were compiled and edited by the present author in <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari">1235</date> / <date calendar="#Gregorian">1819-20</date>
                        </p>
                        <p>The fragment consists of part 1 only out of a total 8 parts</p>
                        <p>Addressees and references include the potentates of <name type="place">Bundelkhand</name> and <name type="place">Malwa</name> provinces from the period of the Second Maratha war; additionally mentions the reduction of Bundelkhand by <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_230011669" role="subject">Colonel John Baillie</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7679" role="subject">General Wellesley</persName>, <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7678" role="subject">General Lord Lake</persName>, and others
                        </p>
                        <p>Defective at end</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
